Get the tile sources for Copernicus GLO-30, ALOS World 3D-30m, NASADEM HGT v001 DTM using the planetary computer STAC catalogue.

Source: R/mpc_srcs.R
mpc_dtm_src.Rd

Get the tile sources for Copernicus GLO-30, ALOS World 3D-30m, NASADEM HGT v001 DTM using the planetary computer STAC catalogue.

Usage

mpc_dtm_src(
  aoi,
  collection = c("cop-dem-glo-30", "cop-dem-glo-90", "alos-dem", "nasadem"),
  vsicurl = TRUE
)

Arguments

aoi

a spatial extent which can be provided as a numeric bounding box or using a spatial object from either the terra, sf or stars packages.

collection

Any of: "cop-dem-glo-30", "cop-dem-glo-90", "alos-dem", "nasadem".

vsicurl

logical with default TRUE. If TRUE the '/vsicurl/' prefix is appended to returned urls which increases read speed for gdal. see https://gdal.org/user/virtual_file_systems.html#vsicurl-http-https-ftp-files-random-access for more information.

Value

A character vector of url paths.

Examples


# define bbox with numeric
mpc_dtm_src(c( -121.772, 45.321, -121.611, 45.419))
#> [1] "/vsicurl/https://elevationeuwest.blob.core.windows.net/copernicus-dem/COP30_hh/Copernicus_DSM_COG_10_N45_00_W122_00_DEM.tif"

if (requireNamespace("sf", quietly = TRUE)){
nc_sf <- system.file("gpkg", "nc.gpkg", package = "sf") |>
sf::read_sf()
mpc_dtm_src(nc_sf, collection = "alos-dem")
}
